# strictly obey these rules:
- run commands from within the project root (AudioSet-Classification/)
- use `uv run pytest` to run tests quickly during development
- use uv for managing dependencies
- prefer `uv run` over running python directly
- when tests pass, use `just test` to do a final slow check
- use absolute imports
- place imports at the top of the file
- use dependency injection
- prefer docstrings over comments
- format code using `just format`

# testing
- use pytest
- prefer test functions to test classes in test files
- use pytest fixtures as input data for things under test
- put shared fixtures in conftest.py files
- use tmp_path to make files and directories in fixtures
- use mocks and patching to isolate the code under test
- focus on the success case when making a new test file
